      "title": "Game 21: Kamsky vs Kasparov (New York 1994)",
      "description": "Illustrative Game for 10 c5. Kasparov challenges White on the queenside, takes control of the dark squares, and constructs a mating net, forcing White's resignation.",
      "textContext": "Pages 64-65 of Starting Out: The King's Indian",
      "preparsedJson": {
        "game_id": "game_21",
        "white": "Kamsky",
        "black": "Kasparov",
        "event": "New York Intel (rapid) 1994",
        "initial_moves": "d4 Nf6 c4 g6 Nc3 Bg7 e4 d6 Nf3 O-O Be2 e5 O-O Nc6 d5 Ne7 b4 Nh5 c5 Nf4",
        "interactive_section": {
